name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: Thanks for having me. I hope today’s chat was helpful. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: Small outdoor gatherings are generally safe as long as some precautions are followed. Since not everyone is fully vaccinated, you should still take steps to protect yourself and others, like wearing a mask if you cannot maintain distance. -AF  https://t.co/61WUS59MiJ

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: Due to these data and more, @US_FDA revoked the authorization of administering bamlanivimab alone. The FDA believes that the other mAb therapies remain appropriate to treat patients with COVID-19. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: In lab studies, some variants reduce the virus’ susceptibility to bamlanivimab and, to a lesser extent, casirivimab & etesevimab. Recent @CDCgov data showed an upsurge of variants expected to be resistant to bamlanivimab administered alone. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: Some variants can cause resistance to one or more of the mAb therapies authorized to treat COVID-19. Combo mAb treatments bamlanivimab+etesevimab or casirivimab+imdevimab are authorized to treat outpatients with COVID-19. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: For most people, benefits of COVID-19 vaccination outweigh the risks. However, those who have had a severe allergic reaction or an immediate allergic reaction to any ingredient in an mRNA COVID-19 vaccine should not get vaccinated. -AF  https://t.co/I6oQAb3hKh

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: .@NIAIDNews has started a study to gather information to help doctors advise people who are highly allergic or have a mast cell disorder about the risks and benefits of receiving the mRNA COVID-19 vaccines. -AF  https://t.co/PdWtmpWjQV

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: This person should wait until they have recovered from illness (if sick) and have met the criteria for discontinuing isolation to receive the 2nd shot. -AF  https://t.co/m4mD4CvHMF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: A report of a condition in VAERS does not mean the condition was caused by the vaccine. VAERS has identified 3 reports of CVST with normal platelet counts out of ~85 million doses of the Moderna vaccine. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: CDC’s Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System has not identified any cases of this combination -- CVST with low blood platelets -- in the more than 180 million doses administered of the Pfizer & Moderna vaccines. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: The @CDCgov & @US_FDA recommended a pause in J&J vaccine administration due to 6 cases of a rare blood clot (cerebral venous sinus thrombosis, or CVST), plus low levels of blood platelets. Treatment of this condition is different from typical treatment for blood clots alone. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: NIH is funding >$1 billion in research to learn more about long-term effects of COVID-19, and ways to treat these outcomes. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: We do not yet understand the risk of developing long-COVID after a breakthrough case of COVID-19 post-vaccination. However, we do know that long-COVID can follow even mild cases of COVID-19. -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: Authorized vaccines are highly effective; however, a small percentage of people fully vaccinated against COVID-19 will still develop COVID-19 illness (called “breakthrough” cases):  https://t.co/g51EBBcDFl -AF

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: By increasing public health departments’ capacity for genomic sequencing, existing and emerging variants could be detected faster -- before they grow prevalent.   This can allow public health officials to implement mitigation measures more quickly to prevent and stop the spread.

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: This investment, made possible by the American Rescue Plan, is critical in our fight against the new and potentially dangerous variants of COVID-19.  Right now, variants account for nearly half of all U.S. COVID-19 cases and we need more capacity to identify and track them.

name: White House COVID-19 Response Team
tweet: 🧵  Today, we are announcing a $1.7 billion investment for the CDC and state and local public health departments to monitor, track, and defeat emerging threats -- whether it’s COVID-19 variants today or other viruses in the future -- through a process known as genomic sequencing.
